Description:
The purpose of this sample is to show how to protect Android application written in Kotlin. Application has two screens : login screen and congrats screen. Login screen asks user to enter the password and congrats screen prints poem string coming from native library.


Installation:
1) Follow documentation to build and install A4A

2) Build SimpleSimon apk using following commands
	cd SimpleSimon
	./gradlew clean build bundle

or if you don't want to build just use pre-built APK or AAB

3) Open blueprint.json or blueprint-aab.json and modify "input" and "output" options in globalConfig to reflect your paths 

4) Execute: 
	protect-android -b blueprint.json
	OR
	protect-android -b blueprint-aab.json for AAB mode

